cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with performance boosting of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in computer vision tasks, specifically through re-calibrating feature maps. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architectural block for boosting performance, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques for improving the performance of CNNs, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed method also involves reducing architectural complexity, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper carries out experiments on datasets, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
